In an isosceles triangle, the base angles are equal. If the given 54° angle is the vertex angle, then the base angles are each \((180° - 54°) / 2 = 63°\). If the given 54° is a base angle, then the other base angle is also 54°, and the vertex angle is \(180° - 2 \times 54° = 72°\).  

Thus, the base angles are either \(63°\) or \(54°\).  

\boxed{63} \text{ or } \boxed{54}
